getPreferredSize() - Method in class com.viaoa.jfc.OAFunctionLabel
public Dimension getPreferredSize() { Dimension d = super.getPreferredSize(); if (isPreferredSizeSet()) return d; int cols = getColumns(); if (cols <= 0) { cols = control.getPropertyInfoDisplayColumns(); } if (cols > 0) { Insets ins = getInsets(); int inx = ins == null ? 0 : ins.left + ins.right; d.width = OAJfcUtil.getCharWidth(cols)+inx+2; } d.height = OATextField.getStaticPreferredHeight(); return d; } public Dimension getMaximumSize() { Dimension d = super.getMaximumSize(); if (isMaximumSizeSet()) return d; int cols = getMaxColumns(); if (cols < 1) { //maxCols = control.getDataSourceMaxColumns(); //if (maxCols < 1) { cols = control.getPropertyInfoMaxLength(); if (cols < 1) { cols = getColumns() * 2; } } Insets ins = getInsets(); int inx = ins == null ? 0 : ins.left + ins.right; if (cols > 0) d.width = OAJfcUtil.getCharWidth(cols) + inx; else { // also check size of text, so that label is not bigger then the text it needs to display String s = getText(); if (s == null) s = " "; FontMetrics fm = getFontMetrics(getFont()); d.width = Math.min(d.width, fm.stringWidth(s)+inx+2); } // dont size under pref size Dimension dx = getPreferredSize(); d.width = Math.max(d.width, dx.width); d.height = OATextField.getStaticPreferredHeight()+2; return d; } public Dimension getMinimumSize() { Dimension d = super.getMinimumSize(); if (isMinimumSizeSet()) return d; int cols = getMiniColumns(); if (cols < 1) return d; d.width = OAJfcUtil.getCharWidth(cols+1); return d; }
